    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-bacon-arrabbiata-farfalle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-bacon-arrabbiata-farfalle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Crush your<strong> garlic </strong>open by squashing them with the side of a knife, then remove the skins and chop roughly</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the dish with your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 30 secs</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-bacon-arrabbiata-farfalle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>with your<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and<strong> </strong>400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-bacon-arrabbiata-farfalle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, add 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> to the dish with your <strong>farfalle</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-bacon-arrabbiata-farfalle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 25 min</p><p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-bacon-arrabbiata-farfalle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta has been cooking for 25 min, remove the dish from the oven</p><p>Stir through your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>oven baked</strong> <strong>spicy bacon arrabbiata farfalle</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-spicy-bacon-arrabbiata-farfalle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, tear your <strong>basil</strong> into the <strong>oven baked spicy bacon arrabbiata farfalle</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>salad</strong> and season with a grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
